==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc}} '''{{polytonic|[[ἀν-]]}}''' (an-) "not" + '''{{polytonic|[[ἀρχός]]}}''' (archos) "leader".

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|GenAm}} {{enPR|ʹănər'kĭzəm}}, {{IPA|/ˈænəɹˌkɪzəm/}}, {{SAMPA|/"{n@r%kIz@m/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# Any theory or doctrine that proposes the [[absence]] of [[government]] in all forms.
# ''Specifically'', a political philosophical belief that all forms of involuntary rule or government are [[undesirable]] or [[unnecessary]] and that society could function without a ruler or involuntary government ([[state]]).

====Derived terms====
* [[anarchist ]]a person that subscribes to the notion that revolution occurs by destroying all authority from within. thus leaving a vacuum from which the needed change may occur. it would be insane to think of anarchy as a final solution. often hopwever it refers to people that have no respect for authority of any kind.

